    {
      "content": "Virtual Network Basics",
      "pos": [
        3,
        25
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What is an Azure Virtual network (VNet)?",
      "pos": [
        31,
        71
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use VNets to provision and manage virtual private networks (VPNs) in Azure and, optionally, link the VNets with other VNets in Azure, or with your on-premises IT infrastructure to create hybrid or cross-premises solutions.",
      "pos": [
        73,
        303
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each VNet you create has its own CIDR block, and can be linked to other VNets and on-premises networks as long as the CIDR blocks do not collide.",
      "pos": [
        304,
        449
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You also have controls of DNS server settings for VNets, and segmentation of the VNet into subnets.",
      "pos": [
        450,
        549
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use VNets to:",
      "pos": [
        552,
        565
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a dedicated private cloud-only virtual network",
      "pos": [
        569,
        622
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Sometimes you don't require a cross-premises configuration for your solution.",
      "pos": [
        664,
        741
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you create a VNet, your services and VMs within your VNet can communicate directly and securely with each other in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        742,
        872
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This keeps traffic securely within the VNet, but still allows you to configure endpoint connections for the VMs and services that require Internet communication as part of your solution.",
      "pos": [
        873,
        1059
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Securely extend your data center",
      "pos": [
        1063,
        1095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With VNets, you can build traditional site-to-site (S2S) VPNs to securely scale your datacenter capacity.",
      "pos": [
        1137,
        1242
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "S2S VPNs use IPSEC to provide a secure connection between your corporate VPN gateway and Azure.",
      "pos": [
        1243,
        1338
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enable hybrid cloud scenarios",
      "pos": [
        1342,
        1371
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "VNets give you the flexibility to support a range of hybrid cloud scenarios.",
      "pos": [
        1413,
        1489
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can securely connect cloud-based applications to any type of on-premises system such as mainframes and Unix systems.",
      "pos": [
        1490,
        1610
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How do I know if I need a virtual network?",
      "pos": [
        1616,
        1658
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1660,
        1865
      ],
      "content": "Visit the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Virtual Network Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/virtual-networks-overview/)</ept> to see a decision table that will help you decide the best network design option for you."
    },
    {
      "content": "How do I get started?",
      "pos": [
        1871,
        1892
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Visit <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>the Virtual Network documentation<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/services/virtual-network/)</ept> to get started.",
      "pos": [
        1894,
        2019
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This page has links to common configuration steps as well as information that will help you understand the things that you'll need to take into consideration when designing your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        2020,
        2214
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What services can I use with VNets?",
      "pos": [
        2220,
        2255
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "VNets can be used with a variety of different Azure services, such as Cloud Services (PaaS), Virtual Machines, and Web Apps.",
      "pos": [
        2257,
        2381
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, there are a few services that are not supported on a VNet.",
      "pos": [
        2382,
        2449
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Please check the specific service you want to use and verify that it is compatible.",
      "pos": [
        2450,
        2533
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I use VNets without cross-premises connectivity?",
      "pos": [
        2539,
        2591
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Yes.",
      "pos": [
        2593,
        2597
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use a VNet without using site-to-site connectivity.",
      "pos": [
        2598,
        2657
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is particularly useful if you want to run domain controllers and SharePoint farms in Azure.",
      "pos": [
        2658,
        2754
      ]
    },
