      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure a virtual network using a network configuration file<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-networks-using-network-configuration-file.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3084,
        3207
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What address ranges can I use in my VNets?",
      "pos": [
        3213,
        3255
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3257,
        3377
      ],
      "content": "You can use public IP address ranges and any IP address range defined in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>RFC 1918<ept id=\"p1\">](http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1918)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I have public IP addresses in my VNets?",
      "pos": [
        3383,
        3426
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Yes.",
      "pos": [
        3428,
        3432
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about public IP address ranges, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Public IP address space in a Virtual Network (VNet)<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-networks-public-ip-within-vnet.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3433,
        3587
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Keep in mind that your public IPs will not be directly accessible from the Internet.",
      "pos": [
        3588,
        3672
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Is there a limit to the number of subnets in my virtual network?",
      "pos": [
        3678,
        3742
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is no limit on the number of subnets you use within a VNet.",
      "pos": [
        3744,
        3809
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All the subnets must be fully contained in the virtual network address space and should not overlap with one another.",
      "pos": [
        3810,
        3927
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Are there any restrictions on using IP addresses within these subnets?",
      "pos": [
        3933,
        4003
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure reserves some IP addresses within each subnet.",
      "pos": [
        4005,
        4057
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The first and last IP addresses of the subnets are reserved for protocol conformance, along with two more addresses used for Azure services.",
      "pos": [
        4058,
        4198
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How small and how large can VNets and subnets be?",
      "pos": [
        4204,
        4253
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The smallest subnet we support is a /29 and the largest is a /8 (using CIDR subnet definitions).",
      "pos": [
        4255,
        4351
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I bring my VLANs to Azure using VNets?",
      "pos": [
        4358,
        4400
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "No.",
      "pos": [
        4402,
        4405
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "VNets are Layer-3 overlays.",
      "pos": [
        4406,
        4433
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure does not support any Layer-2 semantics.",
      "pos": [
        4434,
        4479
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I specify custom routing policies on my VNets and subnets?",
      "pos": [
        4485,
        4547
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Yes.",
      "pos": [
        4549,
        4553
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use User Defined Routing (UDR).",
      "pos": [
        4554,
        4593
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about UDR, visit <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>User Defined Routes and IP Forwarding<ept id=\"p1\">](virtual-networks-udr-overview.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4594,
        4706
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do VNets support multicast or broadcast?",
      "pos": [
        4712,
        4752
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "No.",
      "pos": [
        4754,
        4757
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We do not support multicast or broadcast.",
      "pos": [
        4758,
        4799
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What protocols can I use within VNets?",
      "pos": [
        4805,
        4843
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use standard IP-based protocols within VNets.",
      "pos": [
        4845,
        4898
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, multicast, broadcast, IP-in-IP encapsulated packets and Generic Routing Encapsulation (GRE) packets are blocked within VNets.",
      "pos": [
        4899,
        5033
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Standard protocols that work include:",
      "pos": [
        5034,
        5071
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "TCP",
      "pos": [
        5075,
