    {
      "content": "Yes.",
      "pos": [
        5252,
        5256
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Subnets can be added to VNets at any time as long as the subnet address is not part of another subnet in the VNet.",
      "pos": [
        5257,
        5371
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I modify the size of my VNet size after I create it?",
      "pos": [
        5377,
        5433
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can add, remove, expand or shrink a subnet if there are no VMs or services deployed within it by using PowerShell cmdlets or the NETCFG file.",
      "pos": [
        5435,
        5580
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also add, remove, expand or shrink any prefixes as long as the subnets that contain VMs or services are not affected by the change.",
      "pos": [
        5581,
        5720
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I modify subnets after I created them?",
      "pos": [
        5726,
        5768
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Yes.",
      "pos": [
        5770,
        5774
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can add, remove, and modify the CIDR blocks used by a VNet.",
      "pos": [
        5775,
        5838
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Can I connect to the internet if I am running my services in a VNet?",
      "pos": [
